{
  "texts": [
    "We also noted that several constructs cannot be interpreted without context (e.g., 'lack of evidence', 'shift in focus').",
    "Second, accuracy at the level of edges was generally satisfactory, and most problems would be solved by reversing the edges (i.e., A → B should be B → A).",
    "As a note of concern in the suicide case, GPT views that suicide solves financial problems and chronic pain.",
    "The white paper most certainly did not endorse such views, as it is the prevention package from the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC).",
    "Third, the type of causation is poorly understood across applications, as the system was widely inconsistent (e.g., public health campaigns increased overweight but decreased obesity)."
  ]
}